
" Use `[g` and `]g` to navigate diagnostics
" Use `:CocDiagnostics` to get all diagnostics of current buffer in location lis
[g - (coc-diagnostic-prev)
]g - (coc-diagnostic-next)


" GoTo code navigation
gd - (coc-definition)
gy - (coc-type-definition)
gi - (coc-implementation)
gr - (coc-references)

" Use K to show documentation in preview window
K - :call ShowDocumentation()<CR>

" Symbol renaming
<leader>rn - (coc-rename)

" Applying code actions to the selected code block
" Example: `<leader>aap` for current paragraph
<leader>a - (coc-codeaction-selected)
<leader>a - (coc-codeaction-selected)


" Remap keys for applying code actions at the cursor position
<leader>ac - (coc-codeaction-cursor)

" Apply the most preferred quickfix action to fix diagnostic on the current line
<leader>qf - (coc-fix-current)

" Find symbol of current document
<space>o  :<C-u>CocList outline<cr>

" Show commands
<space>c - :<C-u>CocList commands<cr>
